<div id="review_1302822514" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1302822514" />
    <a title="Marla Munkh-achit" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34195976-marla-munkh-achit"><img alt="Marla Munkh-achit" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1550378822p2/34195976.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1302822514?book_show_action=true">Jun 08, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marla Munkh-achit" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marla Munkh-achit" href="/user/show/34195976-marla-munkh-achit">Marla Munkh-achit</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9780062301260" href="/book/show/22535480-elon-musk">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1302822514" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13855297986497658574">I usually don’t write reviews for books but this time I had to. Elon Musk is arguably one of the best innovators in the Silicon Valley if not the world. Before reading this book, I just thought of him as a rich start-up dude who makes rocket ships and electric cars. I wasn’t wrong about that but this book helped me see all behind the curtains and the struggles he had to overcome to get where he is. When you look at today’s Tesla, you wouldn’t know they were nearly bankrupt in 2008 if it wasn’t f</span>
  <span id="freeText13855297986497658574" style="display:none">I usually don’t write reviews for books but this time I had to. Elon Musk is arguably one of the best innovators in the Silicon Valley if not the world. Before reading this book, I just thought of him as a rich start-up dude who makes rocket ships and electric cars. I wasn’t wrong about that but this book helped me see all behind the curtains and the struggles he had to overcome to get where he is. When you look at today’s Tesla, you wouldn’t know they were nearly bankrupt in 2008 if it wasn’t for Musk. The author did a good job researching his background. You get a pretty good insight of how this man thinks, works and lives. A must read for everyone who is interested in start-ups, technology, space, innovation or this enigmatic individual. I wouldn’t be surprised if one day mankind colonize Mars because of this man’s visions. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13855297986497658574" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


